6. Bartosz, R., Miroslaw, Z., et al. (2014). *A meta-analysis of treatment of vestibular schwannoma using Gamma Knife radiosurgery*. Contemp Oncol, 18(1), 60-66.
7. Carsten, N., Anca, L., et al. (2014). *Stereotactic radiosurgery for brain metastases: A systematic review*. Radiation Oncology, 9, 155.
8. Feng, X., Junjie, Z., et al. (2014). *Stereotactic radiosurgery with and without embolization for intracranial arteriovenous malformations: A systematic review and meta-analysis*. Neurosurg Focus, 37.
9. Leksell, L. (1951). *The stereotaxic method and radiosurgery of the brain*. Acta Chir Scand, 102(4), 316-319.
10. Lunsford, L. D., & Sheehan, J. P. (2016). *Intracranial stereotactic radiosurgery* (Vol. 2).
11. National Comprehensive Cancer Network (NCCN). (2020). *NCCN Clinical Practice Guidelines in Oncology: CNS Tumors* (Version 4).
12. Nida, F., Antonio, M., et al. (2019). *Stereotactic radiosurgery versus stereotactic radiotherapy in the management of intracranial meningiomas: A systematic review and meta-analysis*. Neurosurg Focus, 46.
13. Pinzi, V., et al. (2017). *Radiosurgery for intracranial meningiomas: A systematic review and meta-analysis*. Critical Review in Oncology/Hematology, 113, 122-134.
14. Youmans, J. R., & Winn, H. R. (2011). *Youmans Neurological Surgery*. Philadelphia, PA: Saunders.
15. Zachary, J., Steven, J., et al. (2016). *Stereotactic radiosurgery treatment of trigeminal neuralgia: Clinical outcomes and prognostic factors*. World Neurosurg, 90, 604-612.

